        // ── Overview (Article) ───────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Admin Panel Overview",
            Slug = "admin-overview",
            Summary = "Complete overview of the Admin panel: users, track types, settings, integrations, compliance, training, EDI, events, and more.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 8,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 1,
            AppRoutes = """["/admin"]""",
            Tags = """["admin","overview"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Admin Panel Overview\n\nThe Admin panel is the central configuration hub for QB Engineer. Only users with the Admin role (or Manager for some sub-sections) can access it. Navigate to **Admin** in the sidebar to see all available tabs.\n\n### Users Tab\n\nManage all user accounts. Create new users (the system generates a setup token — admins never set passwords), assign roles, configure kiosk scan identifiers (RFID/NFC/barcode), set avatar colors, and deactivate departing employees. Each user row shows their avatar, name (Last, First format), email, role chip, compliance completion status, and active/inactive indicator.\n\n### Track Types Tab\n\nTrack types define the different kanban boards in the system (Production, R&D/Tooling, Maintenance, etc.). Each track type has an ordered list of stages with names, codes, colors, WIP limits, and irreversibility flags. You can create custom track types for specialized workflows.\n\n### Settings Tab\n\nConfigure company profile (name, phone, email, EIN, website), manage company locations (multiple physical sites with one default), upload your logo, set brand colors, configure pay period locking, and adjust system settings like planning cycle duration and auto-archive timing.\n\n### Integrations Tab\n\nConnect external services: QuickBooks Online (OAuth), shipping carriers (UPS, FedEx, USPS, DHL), SMTP email, and MinIO storage. Each integration card shows its status (Active, Not Configured, Standalone) with Test, Connect, Disconnect, and Configure buttons.\n\n### Terminology Tab\n\nCustomize application labels. If your company calls 'Jobs' something else (like 'Work Orders'), change the label here. Changes apply immediately across the entire app for all users.\n\n### Reference Data Tab\n\nReview all lookup values used in dropdowns throughout the app: expense categories, lead sources, asset types, priorities, and more. Each group is expandable into a read-only table of its items (code, label, effective dates, active status). Values are provisioned through the database (forge-db), not added or edited from this screen.\n\n### Compliance Templates Tab\n\nManage the compliance form templates that employees fill out (W-4, I-9, state withholding, direct deposit, handbook). Upload PDFs for AI-powered field extraction. Monitor employee completion status and approve submissions.\n\n### Training Tab\n\nManage the learning management system. Three sub-tabs: Content (create/edit training modules with Article, Walkthrough, QuickRef, or Quiz types), Paths (organize modules into ordered learning sequences), and Progress (monitor per-user completion).\n\n### Teams & Kiosks Tab\n\nOrganize users into teams with colors and descriptions. Manage kiosk terminals for shop floor displays. Assign team members via checkbox selection.\n\n### Events Tab\n\nCreate and manage company events: meetings, training sessions, safety briefings. Set event type, date/time range, location, attendees, and required/optional status. Events appear on the shop floor display.\n\n### Audit Log Tab\n\nView the complete system audit trail. Every create, update, and delete across all entities is logged with timestamp, user, action, entity type, entity ID, field-level details, and IP address. Filter by entity type, action, user, or date range.\n\n### EDI Tab\n\nManage Electronic Data Interchange: trading partners (X12/EDIFACT), transaction processing, and field mappings. Two sub-tabs: Trading Partners (connection config) and Transactions (processing history with retry).\n\n### MFA Policy Tab\n\nConfigure which roles require multi-factor authentication. View MFA compliance status across all users showing who has MFA enabled and what device type they're using.\n\n### Sales Tax Tab\n\nManage sales tax rates by state/jurisdiction with effective dates. Configure default rates and per-customer overrides.\n\n### Time Corrections Tab\n\nReview and correct employee time entries. Filter by user and date range. View original entry details and create corrections with required reasons that create an audit trail.","sections":[]}"""
        });

