            AppRoutes = """["/admin/reference-data","/admin/terminology"]""",
            Tags = """["admin","reference-data","terminology"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Reference Data and Terminology\n\n### Reference Data\n\nNavigate to **Admin → Reference Data** to manage all lookup values used throughout the application. Reference data groups include:\n\n- **Expense Categories** — the dropdown in the expense form\n- **Lead Sources** — where leads came from (Trade Show, Referral, Website, etc.)\n- **Asset Types** — categories for the asset register\n- **Job Priorities** — the priority options on job cards\n\nEach group is expandable. Click a group to see its current values in a read-only table showing the sort order, code, label, effective-from/to dates, and active status of each entry. This screen is for reviewing what lookup values exist — it does not have in-app Add, Edit, reorder, or delete controls.\n\n### Where Reference Values Come From\n\nReference-data values are provisioned through the database (forge-db) rather than entered here. When you need a new lookup value (a new expense category, lead source, asset type, etc.), or need to change an existing label or its active status, that change is made through the schema/seed-data process — not from this screen. After it is applied, the new or updated value appears here and in the relevant dropdowns across the app. The `code` is immutable once set; it is used internally as the stable identifier.\n\n### Terminology\n\nNavigate to **Admin → Terminology** to customize application labels. If your company calls jobs 'Work Orders' instead of 'Jobs', enter 'Work Orders' next to the `entity_job` key. Click **Save Terminology**.\n\nTerminology changes apply across the entire app — all users see the updated labels immediately. The change is cached in each browser for fast rendering.\n\n### Resetting Labels\n\nDelete the custom text for any terminology key to revert to the system default. The default is derived from the key name (e.g., `entity_job` → 'Job').","sections":[]}"""
