        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Role Templates (Rollups)",
            Slug = "admin-role-templates",
            Summary = "How to bundle several base roles into a single rollup template, assign it on the user form, and understand deletion impact.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 12,
            AppRoutes = """["/admin/role-templates"]""",
            Tags = """["admin","users","roles","role-templates"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Role Templates (Rollups)\n\nForge ships six base roles (Engineer, Production Worker, PM, Manager, Office Manager, Admin). In a small shop one person often wears several hats — the shipping clerk who also receives parts and approves time. **Role templates** (also called *rollups*) let you bundle several base roles under one friendly name so you assign one thing instead of remembering which combination to grant.\n\nNavigate to **Admin → Role Templates** to manage them.\n\n### What a Template Is\n\nA template has a **name**, an optional **description**, and a list of **included roles**. When a user is assigned a template, every role in that list is granted to them in their login claims (JWT). Roles are *additive* — a template that includes Manager and Office Manager grants the union of both, never less.\n\nThe list shows each template's name, description, included-role chips, an **assignee count** (how many users currently hold it), and a System/Custom badge.\n\n### System Defaults vs. Custom\n\nTemplates marked **System** are seeded at install and are **read-only** — they show a lock icon instead of edit/delete buttons. They give every install a sensible starting set. To customize, create your own **Custom** template; only Custom templates can be edited or deleted.\n\n### Creating a Template\n\nClick **New Template**. Enter a name (max 100 chars) and optional description, then pick at least one role in **Included Roles** (a multi-select). Click **Create Template**. The rollup is now available on the user form.\n\n### Assigning a Template on the User Form\n\nRole templates are assigned per-user in **Admin → Users**. Edit (or create) a user and look for the **Role Template (Rollup)** dropdown — it appears only when at least one template exists. It is optional: pick a rollup if the user wears many hats, or leave it blank to rely on the single base **Role** field alone. The user's avatar row then shows a chip naming the template and the roles it expands to.\n\n### Deletion Impact\n\nDeleting a Custom template does **not** delete or deactivate the users who held it — it simply removes the rollup. Those users keep their base **Role** but lose the extra roles the template was granting at login. Re-grant access by assigning a different template or by editing each user's base role. Because of this ripple effect, check the **assignee count** before deleting: a template with many assignees should be retired deliberately, not on a whim.\n\n### When to Use a Template vs. the Base Role\n\nUse the single base **Role** when a person fits one of the six roles cleanly. Reach for a template only when the same multi-role combination recurs across several people — then a named rollup is easier to assign consistently and audit than hand-picking roles each time.","sections":[]}"""
        });

