            AppRoutes = """["/admin/settings"]""",
            Tags = """["admin","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"Advanced, edge-case notes for the admin configuration area. This is scannable reference material, not a walkthrough — it documents the ancillary mechanics behind reference data, identity, integrations, and company settings.\n\n## Reference Data & Terminology\n\n- **Effective-date windowing.** Each `reference_data` row carries optional `EffectiveFrom` / `EffectiveTo` (`timestamptz`). A value is in force only inside that window; outside it the entry is hidden from dropdowns even while the row still exists. Use windowing for things like a tax-year category that should appear only for a period. `IsActive=false` hides a value unconditionally regardless of dates.\n- **Grouping & metadata model.** Lookups live in one `reference_data` table partitioned by `GroupCode` (e.g. `part.item_kind`, expense categories, lead sources). Rows can self-nest via `ParentId` for recursive groups, order within a group by `SortOrder`, and carry arbitrary structured extras in the `Metadata` JSONB column. `Code` is the immutable stable identifier; `Label` is the display text.\n- **Where values are created.** The Reference Data tab is **read-only** — there is no in-app Add/Edit/reorder/delete. New or changed lookups are provisioned through the database (**forge-db** declarative schema / seed-data) and the `IsSeedData` flag marks seed-provisioned rows. After the schema is applied the value appears here and in the relevant dropdowns.\n- **Kiosk / anonymous reads.** Reference reads are exposed on unauthenticated surfaces (shop-floor kiosk, display) so dropdowns and labels render before a user signs in — these reads return only active, in-window rows.\n- **Terminology key prefixes.** Terminology overrides are keyed with conventional prefixes — `entity_*` (e.g. `entity_job` → 'Jobs'), with the default label derived from the key name when no override is set. Saving an override applies app-wide immediately and is cached per browser; deleting the custom text reverts to the derived default.\n\n## Users / Roles / Teams\n\n- **RFID WebHID pairing.** The Users tab can bind an RFID/NFC reader in-browser via WebHID; the page shows a connected/disconnected indicator and offers a **Download RFID setup script** for the relay that feeds scans to kiosk terminals. Scans land as `UserScanIdentifier` rows (RFID / NFC / Barcode / Biometric).\n- **Employee barcode generation.** A user's badge barcode is generated from their scan identifier so it can be printed and later scanned at a kiosk for Tier-2 (badge + PIN) auth.\n- **Kiosk terminals & team-delete dependency.** Kiosk terminals are paired to a team (Teams & Kiosks tab). Because terminals and swimlanes depend on a team, deleting a team is gated/confirmed and never deletes the member users — it only removes the team and its associations.\n- **Work Location visibility & state withholding.** The **Work Location** field on the user form appears only when more than one `CompanyLocation` exists. The chosen location (or the default when null) drives which **state withholding** compliance forms the employee must complete.\n\n## Integrations / Connections\n\n- **Mode change requires a restart.** Switching the accounting provider mode (Standalone ⇄ a connected provider) is an install-level change that takes effect on the next API restart; it is not a hot toggle. Plan provider switches as a maintenance action.\n- **Capability gating + disabled banner.** The Connections registry and the API-key tabs are gated by **CAP-IDEN-AUTH-API-KEYS**; the audit-log read is gated by **CAP-IDEN-AUDIT-SYSTEM-LOG**. When a gating capability is off, the New-Key/action controls are disabled and a banner explains why; the table stays empty.\n- **Registry status vocabulary & scoping.** `/admin/connections` is a read-only federated audit view. Each row's **Owner** is the user email for user-scoped credentials or **Install-level** for whole-install connections. Status words are color-mapped: green = Active/Connected/Linked; amber = Expired; neutral = Revoked/Disconnected/Inactive. The registry never mutates — the **Manage** button deep-links to each connection's native admin surface.\n- **Carrier cards vs /admin/carriers.** Shipping-carrier *credentials* live only on **/admin/carriers** (Test button = `POST /carriers/{id}/test`). The Integrations page may surface carrier cards for status, but credential entry and the per-carrier test belong to the Carriers admin, not the integrations descriptors.\n- **MOCK_INTEGRATIONS & sandbox.** The `MOCK_INTEGRATIONS` env var (true in Development) bypasses every external API with simulated responses — useful for setup/testing without live credentials. Provider sandbox setup and developer-portal links are surfaced as guidance for getting real credentials before going live.\n\n## Company Settings / Audit / API keys\n\n- **Audit retention & immutability.** Audit-log entries are append-only — no user can edit or delete them. Default retention is ~90 days (configurable in system settings). Read via `GET /api/v1/admin/audit-log` (gated by CAP-IDEN-AUDIT-SYSTEM-LOG); CSV export supports external-audit reconciliation.\n- **System-event presets vs free-text.** The Audit Log **Action** filter accepts both the common preset verbs (Create / Update / Delete, login events) and free-text, so you can filter on either a known system event or an exact action string.\n- **API-key role-template inheritance & no-self-issue.** Every System/BI API key is bound to a real user and authenticates *as* that user; an optional **Role Template** narrows the key's effective roles below the owner's full set (inheritance flows user → template → key). The identity a key authenticates as is deliberately denied the key-issuing endpoint — **keys cannot issue keys** — so a leaked key can't escalate by minting more. Secrets are shown **once** at issue (hash-only storage thereafter).\n- **Settings secret masking.** Stored integration secrets and credentials are masked in the settings UI and never returned in plaintext to the client — only presence/last-used metadata is exposed.\n- **Track-type accounting & irreversibility.** A `JobStage` may carry an `AccountingDocumentType?` (e.g. Invoice, Payment) and an `IsIrreversible` flag. When a stage produces an accounting document, marking it irreversible prevents jobs from moving backward past it, protecting financial consistency — the accounting-document type is what justifies the irreversibility, so the two are configured together.","sections":[]}"""
